title: Shobana Jeyasingh Dance: We Caliban review – postcolonial take on The Tempest is difficult to pin down
summary: Jeyasingh’s choreography is skillfully crafted and executed, but the character Caliban's challenges seem lost among the multitude of concepts presented. The performance showcases technical excellence yet lacks focus in conveying Caliban's narrative. Overall, while impressive, the piece feels unanchored.

title: Police looking into claims Prince Andrew asked officer to find information on Virginia Giuffre
